	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> <date>Elul 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5589</date></p>
				<p>To <addressee>Messrs Joseph S. Cohen</addressee> &#38;<lb/> <addressee>S. M. Goldsmidt</addressee></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">committee in behalf of the K. K. M. Israel.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Gentlemen.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Permit me to transmit through you to the members of<lb/> the K. K. M. I. my acceptance of the office of Hazan&#44; to which office<lb/> they did me the honour to elect me on yesterday.  In accepting this<lb/> highly responsible station I am fully alive to the various&#44; and in a<lb/> measure&#44; new duties&#44; which devolve on me.  No man <add>can be</add> more <add>aware</add> than my&#45;<lb/>self&#44; <del>can be aware</del> of my want of qualifications to acquit myself pro&#45;<lb/>perly&#59; but it shall be my constant aim&#44; to merit the indulgence if<lb/> not the confidence of this respectable congregation&#44; but attending strictly<lb/> as far as lies in my power&#44; to the duties of my office&#44; so that I may<lb/> never be accused of carelessness and negligence.  It would be unbecoming<lb/> in me to be more particular&#44; as I do not consider it right to make<lb/> promises&#44; which I might be unable to <sic>fulfil</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Accept for yourself my sincere thanks for the highly flattering<lb/> manner in which you announced to me the result of the election&#59;<lb/> and be assured&#44; that your prosperity and the prosperity of the com&#45;<lb/>munity you represent&#44; will ever be gratifying</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">to your and the congregation&#39;s</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">very obedient servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">May God preserve you&#33;</p>
		</body>
